OL,5,Cbooze?
OL,7,FBilirubin is one of the measurements
OL,8,Fused to assess liver health. It's a
OL,9,Fyellow substance that forms as a by-
OL,10,Fproduct when old red cells are broken
OL,11,Fdown. Too much of it turns you
OL,12,Fjaundice. A healthy range is anywhere
OL,13,Fbetween 0 ` 21.
OL,15,FWhen I was admitted to Kings in 2015
OL,16,Fmy bilirubin was 403. It's now 8. An
OL,17,Fultrasound revealed my liver is no
OL,18,Flonger fatty or enlarged. And, perhaps
OL,19,Fmost incredible of all, a fibroscan
OL,20,Fshowed my liver is no longer scarred.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G32/35
